{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Branch staleness detection correctly identifies branches with commits not in main, older than the configured age threshold, and no open PR.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is real git + PR-state reality, not just pure logic. REAL-INFRA applies because validating \"commits not in main\" and commit age typically depends on actual git history/subprocess behavior; MOCK-HIDE risk is high if commit topology is faked. LLM-DEP and MULTI-STEP do not apply.","test_description":"Create a temporary real git repo, create main and feature history with controlled commit dates, ensure feature has no open PR in the real/staging PR source used by the app (or a real local equivalent service), run staleness detection end-to-end, and assert it returns stale for the feature branch only when age threshold is exceeded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.33,"System":0.52,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Session-start setup emits a stale-work warning with actionable branch context when the current branch is stale.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is cross-module orchestration (session bootstrap wiring + detector result + warning renderer), but does not require real OS/network/subprocess if detector output is injected. REJECTION-GATE: considered System, rejected because behavior text only requires emitting warning \"when the current branch is stale,\" not validating real git/PR discovery itself.","test_description":"Wire session-start bootstrap with real in-process modules and a deterministic stale-branch detector stub returning stale context (branch name, age, ahead count). Assert warning is emitted once with actionable context fields and expected wording marker.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A local status-classifier function maps computed branch state to labels (`clean`, `stale-no-pr`) deterministically.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Single local function mapping precomputed state to enum-like labels; no module handoff, infra, or model dependency. Higher levels are unnecessary for this behavior.","test_description":"Call classifier directly with representative state fixtures (clean, stale-without-pr, boundary values) and assert exact label outputs and deterministic repeatability across runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"`/kaizen-wip` against live repo and PR state distinguishes \"clean\" from \"has commits but no PR (STALE)\" in rendered output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly says \"against live repo and PR state,\" so REAL-INFRA is required (real git/HTTP/API path). In-process fakes can hide failures in command/API integration and rendering under real data shapes. No LLM dependency.","test_description":"Run `/kaizen-wip` in a real test repo connected to real or test PR backend state, exercise one clean branch and one branch with unPR'd commits, and assert rendered output contains the correct status line for each case.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Branches with open or merged PRs are not flagged as stale-no-PR false positives.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is state handoff across staleness logic + PR-status interpretation modules; in-process wiring with realistic PR-status fixtures can catch this. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no mandatory real OS/network from behavior text, (b) no AI output, (c) no multi-agentic chain. REJECTION-GATE: considered System, rejected because behavior text does not require live API, only correctness for open/merged states.","test_description":"Run staleness pipeline in-process with realistic branch metadata plus PR states (`open`, `merged`) from fixture adapters; assert final status is not `stale-no-pr` for either state while still flagging true no-PR cases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.56,"System":0.28,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change but branch state should no longer be classified as unPRed stale work.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure appears in real git graph evolution (rebases/squash merges rewrite ancestry and hashes). MOCK-MISS and REAL-INFRA indicate subprocess/git-object behavior is the true boundary; faked commit sets often miss ancestry edge cases.","test_description":"In a real temporary git repo, create branch commits, simulate PR-equivalent integration via squash merge and separately rebase scenarios, then run detector and assert branch is not classified `stale-no-pr` after integration despite hash changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
